TECprogress

Fabian Blombach

18/10/2019

This script describes the generation of generalised linear models for the progression of TEC-Spt4/5 to TEC-Spt4/5-Elf1 during oxidative stress. Negative binomial models were used to model count data that showed overdispersion. Raw coverage of Elf1 in the promoter region was modelled. The normalisation against the chromatin input was built into the model by including an offest term with raw chromatin input coverage.

# loop to make table with dinucleotides

for (j in 1:nrow(mono)) {
  for (i in 1:(ncol(mono)-1)) { 
  dinuc[j,i] <- paste0(mono[j,i], mono[j,i+1]) 
  } 
}

dinucG[dinucG == NN[k,1]]<- NN[k,4]
}

# replace monocleotides with corresponding deltaG values for terminal nucleotides
monoG<-as.matrix(mono, nrow=nrow(mono))

}

Automatic model selection with step() function including binary interaction terms

#function to calculate BIC
bic<-function(model) {-model$twologlik  + (length(model$coefficients)+1) * log(nrow(model$model))}

model.null<- suppressWarnings(glm.nb(Elf1_r1_promCov ~ offset(log(Inp1_promCov)), data=data.mod))
#full model including all binary interaction terms
model.bin <- suppressWarnings(glm.nb(Elf1_r1_promCov ~ offset(log(Inp1_promCov)) + log(spt45_r1_promoter) + deltaG + log(TFB1_foldR1) + log(TFEb_foldR1) + log(cpsf1_r1_promoter) + I(log(spt45_r1_promoter)*deltaG) + I(log(spt45_r1_promoter)*log(TFB1_foldR1)) + I(log(spt45_r1_promoter)*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(log(spt45_r1_promoter)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(deltaG*log(TFB1_foldR1)) + I(deltaG*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(deltaG*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(log(TFB1_foldR1)*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(log(TFB1_foldR1)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(log(TFEb_foldR1)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)), data=data.Merged2))

model.step<-step(object=model.null, scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=model.null$call), data=data.mod, trace=F, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(data.mod)))
bic(model.step)
## [1] 1244.338
#trying to add single terms to starting model
model.step.spt45<-step(object=update(model.null,  ~ . + log(spt45_r1_promoter)), scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=~1), data=data.mod, trace=F, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(data.mod)))
bic(model.step.spt45)
## [1] 1244.338
model.step.deltaG<-step(object=update(model.null,  ~ . + deltaG), scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=~1), data=data.mod, trace=F, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(data.mod)))
bic(model.step.deltaG)
## [1] 1242.648
model.step.TFB<-step(object=update(model.null,  ~ . + log(TFB1_foldR1)), scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=~1), data=data.mod, trace=F, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(data.mod)))
bic(model.step.TFB)
## [1] 1242.648

bic(model.step.TFEb)
## [1] 1246.612
